<qti-assessment-item xmlns="http://www.imsglobal.org/xsd/imsqtiasi_v3p0" xmlns:m="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" identifier="Q28_v8" title="Q28_v8" time-dependent="false" adaptive="false" xsi:schemaLocation="http://www.imsglobal.org/xsd/imsqtiasi_v3p0 https://purl.imsglobal.org/spec/qti/v3p0/schema/xsd/imsqti_asiv3p0_v1p0.xsd">
  <qti-response-declaration identifier="RESPONSE" cardinality="single" base-type="identifier">
    <qti-correct-response>
      <qti-value>ChoiceB</qti-value>
    </qti-correct-response>
  </qti-response-declaration>
  <qti-outcome-declaration identifier="FEEDBACK" cardinality="single" base-type="identifier"/>
  <qti-outcome-declaration identifier="SOLUTION" cardinality="single" base-type="identifier"/>
  <qti-outcome-declaration identifier="SCORE" cardinality="single" base-type="float">
    <qti-default-value>
      <qti-value>0</qti-value>
    </qti-default-value>
  </qti-outcome-declaration>
  <qti-item-body>
    <p>Al imprimir piezas con resina en una impresora 3D, la rapidez r, medida en centímetros cúbicos por hora (cm³/h), se modela con la expresión</p>
    <p>
      <m:math>
        <m:mi>r</m:mi>
        <m:mo>=</m:mo>
        <m:mfrac>
          <m:mi>V</m:mi>
          <m:mi>t</m:mi>
        </m:mfrac>
      </m:math>,
      donde V es el volumen total de la pieza, en cm³, y t es el tiempo total de impresión, en horas.
    </p>
    <p>Para una pieza se programan 100 cm³ de resina con una rapidez de 250 cm³/h. ¿Cuántos minutos durará la impresión de esta pieza?</p>
    <qti-choice-interaction response-identifier="RESPONSE" shuffle="true" max-choices="1">
      <qti-simple-choice identifier="ChoiceA">40 minutos<qti-feedback-inline identifier="FB_ChoiceA" outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK">Incorrecto. Si <m:math><m:mi>r</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mfrac><m:mi>V</m:mi><m:mi>t</m:mi></m:mfrac></m:math>, entonces <m:math><m:mi>t</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mfrac><m:mi>V</m:mi><m:mi>r</m:mi></m:mfrac><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mfrac><m:mn>100</m:mn><m:mn>250</m:mn></m:mfrac><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>0,4</m:mn></m:math> horas. Al convertir a minutos, <m:math><m:mn>0,4</m:mn><m:mo>×</m:mo><m:mn>60</m:mn><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>24</m:mn></m:math> minutos. Por lo tanto, 40 minutos no corresponde al tiempo de impresión.</qti-feedback-inline></qti-simple-choice>
      <qti-simple-choice identifier="ChoiceB">24 minutos<qti-feedback-inline identifier="FB_ChoiceB" outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK">¡Correcto! De <m:math><m:mi>r</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mfrac><m:mi>V</m:mi><m:mi>t</m:mi></m:mfrac></m:math> se obtiene <m:math><m:mi>t</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mfrac><m:mi>V</m:mi><m:mi>r</m:mi></m:mfrac></m:math>. Entonces <m:math><m:mi>t</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mfrac><m:mn>100</m:mn><m:mn>250</m:mn></m:mfrac><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>0,4</m:mn></m:math> horas. Como <m:math><m:mn>1</m:mn><m:mtext> hora </m:mtext><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>60</m:mn><m:mtext> minutos</m:mtext></m:math>, resulta <m:math><m:mn>0,4</m:mn><m:mo>×</m:mo><m:mn>60</m:mn><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>24</m:mn></m:math> minutos.</qti-feedback-inline></qti-simple-choice>
      <qti-simple-choice identifier="ChoiceC">150 minutos<qti-feedback-inline identifier="FB_ChoiceC" outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK">Incorrecto. El tiempo se calcula con <m:math><m:mi>t</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mfrac><m:mi>V</m:mi><m:mi>r</m:mi></m:mfrac></m:math>. Sustituyendo los datos, <m:math><m:mi>t</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mfrac><m:mn>100</m:mn><m:mn>250</m:mn></m:mfrac><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>0,4</m:mn></m:math> horas, y eso equivale a <m:math><m:mn>0,4</m:mn><m:mo>×</m:mo><m:mn>60</m:mn><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>24</m:mn></m:math> minutos. Por lo tanto, 150 minutos no satisface el problema.</qti-feedback-inline></qti-simple-choice>
      <qti-simple-choice identifier="ChoiceD">250 minutos<qti-feedback-inline identifier="FB_ChoiceD" outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK">Incorrecto. Con la fórmula <m:math><m:mi>r</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mfrac><m:mi>V</m:mi><m:mi>t</m:mi></m:mfrac></m:math>, el tiempo es <m:math><m:mi>t</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mfrac><m:mi>V</m:mi><m:mi>r</m:mi></m:mfrac><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mfrac><m:mn>100</m:mn><m:mn>250</m:mn></m:mfrac><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>0,4</m:mn></m:math> horas. Luego, <m:math><m:mn>0,4</m:mn><m:mo>×</m:mo><m:mn>60</m:mn><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>24</m:mn></m:math> minutos. Así, 250 minutos no es el tiempo de impresión de esta pieza.</qti-feedback-inline></qti-simple-choice>
    </qti-choice-interaction>
    <qti-feedback-block identifier="show" outcome-identifier="SOLUTION" show-hide="show">
      <qti-content-body>
        <p><strong>Resolución paso a paso</strong></p>
        <ol>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Paso 1: Identificar los datos del problema</strong></p>
            <p>El volumen total de la pieza es 100 cm³ y la rapidez de impresión es 250 cm³/h.</p>
            <p>La fórmula dada es <m:math><m:mi>r</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mfrac><m:mi>V</m:mi><m:mi>t</m:mi></m:mfrac></m:math>.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Paso 2: Despejar el tiempo</strong></p>
            <p>De la relación <m:math><m:mi>r</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mfrac><m:mi>V</m:mi><m:mi>t</m:mi></m:mfrac></m:math>, se obtiene <m:math><m:mi>t</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mfrac><m:mi>V</m:mi><m:mi>r</m:mi></m:mfrac></m:math>.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Paso 3: Sustituir los valores</strong></p>
            <p><m:math><m:mi>t</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mfrac><m:mn>100</m:mn><m:mn>250</m:mn></m:mfrac></m:math></p>
            <p><m:math><m:mi>t</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>0,4</m:mn></m:math> horas.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Paso 4: Convertir horas a minutos</strong></p>
            <p>Como 1 hora equivale a 60 minutos, se multiplica por 60:</p>
            <p><m:math><m:mn>0,4</m:mn><m:mo>×</m:mo><m:mn>60</m:mn><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>24</m:mn></m:math></p>
            <p>Entonces, el tiempo de impresión es 24 minutos.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Conclusión</strong></p>
            <p>La alternativa correcta es <strong>24 minutos</strong>, es decir, la opción B.</p>
          </li>
        </ol>
      </qti-content-body>
    </qti-feedback-block>
  </qti-item-body>
  <qti-response-processing>
    <qti-response-condition>
      <qti-response-if>
        <qti-match>
          <qti-variable identifier="RESPONSE"/>
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">ChoiceB</qti-base-value>
        </qti-match>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SCORE">
          <qti-base-value base-type="float">1</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceB</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-if>
      <qti-response-else-if>
        <qti-match>
          <qti-variable identifier="RESPONSE"/>
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">ChoiceA</qti-base-value>
        </qti-match>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceA</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-else-if>
      <qti-response-else-if>
        <qti-match>
          <qti-variable identifier="RESPONSE"/>
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">ChoiceC</qti-base-value>
        </qti-match>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceC</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-else-if>
      <qti-response-else-if>
        <qti-match>
          <qti-variable identifier="RESPONSE"/>
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">ChoiceD</qti-base-value>
        </qti-match>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceD</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-else-if>
      <qti-response-else>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceA</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-else>
    </qti-response-condition>
  </qti-response-processing>
</qti-assessment-item>